value.0: Diatium power cells, used in lightsabers, contain extremely concentrated amounts of trumponium gas that forms a plasma rod when heated. The beam of plasma produces from a lightsaber is contained by a type of magnetic or energy field that recycles the energy back into the diatium power cell when not in contact with other lightsabers or objects. This greatly conserves the energy of a diatium power cell, but now and then it still needs replacement. Due to the power cell's natural recharging abilities (recharge socket usually required), makes it ideal for a melee weapon such as a lightsaber. If assembled correctly, power cell should last indefinitely and require no further maintenance from the operator.
